  "prompt": "What is the best app to keep track of your daily expense?",
  "response": "There are several good apps for tracking daily expenses, and the \"best\" can depend on individual needs. However, here are some top-rated options:\n\n1. Mint\n- Free\n- Automatically categorizes transactions\n- Budgeting and bill tracking\n- Syncs with bank accounts\n\n2. YNAB (You Need A Budget)\n- Paid app\n- Detailed budgeting features\n- Helps create financial goals\n- Teaches budgeting principles\n\n3. Personal Capital\n- Free\n- Investment tracking\n- Expense tracking\n- Net worth calculation\n\n4. Expensify\n- Good for business and personal expenses\n- Receipt scanning\n- Expense report generation\n- Multi-platform support\n\n5. PocketGuard\n- Free and paid versions\n- Shows how much money is available to spend\n- Tracks bills and subscriptions\n- Simple interface\n\n6. Goodbudget\n- Uses envelope budgeting method\n- Sync across multiple devices\n- Free and paid versions\n- Manual entry focused\n\n7. Clarity Money\n- Free\n- Helps find ways to save money\n- Tracks spending\n- Cancels unnecessary subscriptions\n\nThe best choice depends on your specific needs, budget, and preferences. I recommend trying a few to see which fits your style.",
